# GnuTLS CVEs in Debian 12 (bookworm) runtime images.
#
# All DCC services use debian:12-slim as the runtime base and install libpq5,
# which pulls in libgnutls30 as a transitive dependency. None of our services
# use GnuTLS or DTLS directly — they connect to local PostgreSQL over TCP and
# to the DCC node over gRPC (backed by hyper/tonic, not GnuTLS).
#
# These CVEs are pending Debian 12 security backport. Track at:
# https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/source-package/gnutls28
#
# Justification filed: 2026-06-09. Review when Debian releases the backport.

CVE-2026-42009
CVE-2026-3833
CVE-2026-33846
CVE-2026-42010
CVE-2026-33845

# OpenSSL heap use-after-free in PKCS7_verify() — CVE-2026-45447
#
# Affects libssl3t64 / libssl3 in Ubuntu Noble (24.04) base images used by
# eclipse-temurin JVM images (matcher, node-scala).
#
# The JVM services do not perform PKCS7 verification — they use TLS for network
# connections (gRPC, HTTPS) but never parse PKCS7 structures from untrusted input.
# Attack surface: none for these workloads.
#
# Fixed upstream in OpenSSL 3.5.7-r0 (Alpine) and in Node.js alpine images.
# Ubuntu Noble backport pending. Track at:
# https://ubuntu.com/security/CVE-2026-45447
#
# Justification filed: 2026-06-19. Remove when eclipse-temurin ships fixed base.
CVE-2026-45447
